13:50.443 --> 13:52.104
ALEX: Sorry, Bug, sorry.

13:52.645 --> 13:53.873
You're good?

13:53.946 --> 13:56.414
He's still alive. It's okay.
Grab my hand.

13:56.482 --> 13:58.473
I'm blind, Bug.
Not you.

13:58.718 --> 14:00.117
You good?
Who's this?

14:00.186 --> 14:01.244
JEROME: It's not cool.

14:01.387 --> 14:02.684
ALEX: Why the hell
are there cops here?

14:02.755 --> 14:03.881
JAY: Jerome, big log. Big log.

14:03.956 --> 14:05.014
(BOYS LAUGHING)

14:05.091 --> 14:06.558
(CHATTER ON POLICE RADIO)

14:06.626 --> 14:07.650
Get down.

14:07.727 --> 14:10.025
What the fuck was that?
Why did they stop us?

14:10.096 --> 14:11.358
POLICEMAN: Go home!

14:11.831 --> 14:14.732
Ripper Day has been
officially canceled.

14:14.834 --> 14:17.598
JAY: Just better sit and wait.
Why so glum, chum?

14:17.937 --> 14:19.302
I failed.

14:19.372 --> 14:21.397
Because you
couldn't kill him?

14:21.474 --> 14:23.271
Now we're all going to die,
and it's my fault.

14:23.342 --> 14:25.469
No!
That's bullshit
Brandon made up.

14:25.778 --> 14:28.008
If he was so worried
about it, he should
have killed it himself.

14:28.080 --> 14:29.513
That puppet was scary.
Thanks.

14:29.615 --> 14:32.550
And the coat was creepy.
You added some moss
and grass and shit, right?

14:32.618 --> 14:34.916
Yeah, man,
he lived under the
river for like 16 years.

14:34.987 --> 14:36.215
He's primeval, baby!

14:36.289 --> 14:38.018
If he rode in an ambulance
on the way to the hospital,

14:38.090 --> 14:39.352
how did he get the coat
and everything?

14:40.059 --> 14:43.392
ln my version,
the day after Plenkov
supposedly drowned

14:43.563 --> 14:44.757
his house was
burglarized, right?

14:44.830 --> 14:47.230
And he took the boots,
the coat, his whole outfit.

14:47.300 --> 14:48.528
Why would a burglar
just take clothes?

14:48.701 --> 14:50.168
A burglar wouldn't, Bug.

14:50.236 --> 14:52.329
But Plenkov would,
if he was still alive!

14:52.638 --> 14:54.105
Exactly!
The Ripper's alive?

14:54.207 --> 14:55.731
ALEX: Could be.
I thought you said
he was just a ghost.

14:55.808 --> 14:57.036
No, he's dead.

14:57.109 --> 14:59.703
No. Not necessarily.
They never found his body.

14:59.779 --> 15:01.679
And nobody really knew him
or his wife very well.

15:01.847 --> 15:02.973
They were new to Riverton.
Yeah.

15:03.049 --> 15:06.246
And, Plenkov could look
completely different
after 16 years!

15:06.319 --> 15:10.016
Like, cosmetic surgery,
hair transplants,
Weight Watchers.

15:10.223 --> 15:11.554
And he could have
changed his name.

15:11.624 --> 15:13.683
Snuck back into Riverton
to get his revenge this year.

15:13.759 --> 15:15.056
He could be
Principal Pratt!

15:15.528 --> 15:17.189
Shut the fuck up!

15:17.663 --> 15:19.290
I got to get home, guys.

15:21.667 --> 15:23.498
Wait, are you guys
set for tomorrow?

15:23.569 --> 15:25.332
For what?
JAY: The buzzard thing
or whatever.

15:25.538 --> 15:26.630
Condor.

15:26.706 --> 15:27.798
Yeah, we made
a sock puppet.

15:27.873 --> 15:30.171
A sock puppet?
You'll put your
class to sleep!

15:30.243 --> 15:31.938
A good show-and-tell
needs shock-and-awe!

15:32.011 --> 15:35.447
It's my fault.
I was too scared about
tonight to think about it.

15:35.514 --> 15:36.811
Listen, Bug.

15:36.882 --> 15:38.577
I'm scared of the Ripper, too.
You are?

15:38.651 --> 15:40.676
I got to cross that
bridge twice a day.

15:40.753 --> 15:41.879
I do what my
grandma taught me.

15:41.954 --> 15:44.616
Spit in the river, and
he won't come after me.

15:44.690 --> 15:46.715
That works?
Yeah, for 16 years.

15:47.059 --> 15:48.185
See you, guys!

15:48.261 --> 15:49.489
See you.

15:50.529 --> 15:51.757
I got to go.

15:51.931 --> 15:53.296
We should go, too.

15:53.566 --> 15:56.091
Quint is going
to kill me if he catches
me out this late.

15:56.168 --> 15:57.635
BOBBY: I don't know
about this new curfew.

15:57.703 --> 15:59.102
We should've let
them kill him first.

15:59.171 --> 16:00.229
PATERSON: Kill who?

16:01.407 --> 16:02.669
Plenkov.

16:03.876 --> 16:05.070
The Ripper.

16:05.244 --> 16:06.404
Very creative.

16:06.479 --> 16:08.413
That's why
every kid in Riverton
has Ripper nightmares

16:08.514 --> 16:10.505
and the adults have
memorial services.

16:10.583 --> 16:13.416
It's time to move on!
Leave the past behind.

16:13.486 --> 16:15.181
Come on.
Let's get out of here.

16:15.254 --> 16:16.721
PATERSON: I'm glad
they're getting rid of it.

16:16.789 --> 16:18.154
Rid of what?

16:18.224 --> 16:19.782
That damn ambulance.

16:20.293 --> 16:21.988
Pratt, the new principal
at the high school

16:22.061 --> 16:24.621
convinced
the chamber of commerce
it was bad for tourism.

16:24.697 --> 16:26.358
What?

16:26.432 --> 16:29.890
No, no, no! It's a memorial.
That's why it's still here.

16:29.969 --> 16:33.234
Tourism, Bob.
Tourism is where
everything is going.

16:35.908 --> 16:36.966
''Let's go to Riverton, honey,

16:37.076 --> 16:40.136
''where that crazy fucker
killed seven people
and his wife.''

16:40.212 --> 16:41.543
Not.

16:47.520 --> 16:49.818
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

17:17.616 --> 17:19.550
(RUSTLING)

17:27.425 --> 17:28.791
JAY: What the hell?

17:36.235 --> 17:38.931
(GRUFFLY)
Fear ye the Ripper!

17:39.405 --> 17:41.600
I spit in the river!
I spit in the river!

17:41.674 --> 17:42.800
Bug!

17:43.042 --> 17:44.134
Alex!

17:44.210 --> 17:46.269
No! Please, no!

17:50.049 --> 17:51.573
(GRUNTS)

17:52.184 --> 17:53.173
(SCREAMING)

17:54.286 --> 17:55.685
(GASPING)

18:00.526 --> 18:02.289
What just happened?

18:12.571 --> 18:14.198
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

18:18.677 --> 18:19.666
(DOOR OPENS)

18:21.080 --> 18:22.945
QUlNT: You better
be in bed.

18:23.449 --> 18:24.438
(DOOR CLOSES)

18:24.750 --> 18:27.218
I'll kick your punk ass
if you ain't!

18:27.286 --> 18:30.153
If you fuck with me,
you'll be sorry!

18:30.222 --> 18:31.917
Shithead!

18:31.991 --> 18:33.754
Fear ye the Ripper.

18:33.826 --> 18:35.293
(THUNDER CLAPPlNG)

18:37.263 --> 18:38.525
DR. COOPER ON RADIO:
The California Condors

18:38.597 --> 18:40.030
are magnificent birds.

18:40.099 --> 18:44.229
They can fly 15,000 feet high,
cruise at 55 miles per hour

18:44.303 --> 18:47.238
and cover 150 miles
in a single day.

18:47.306 --> 18:51.242
And they're so big,
they're often mistaken
for small airplanes on radar.

18:51.310 --> 18:53.437
I mean... I mean,
they're huge.

18:54.313 --> 18:55.541
FEMALE RADIO HOST:
That's amazing.

18:55.614 --> 18:57.172
You're listening
to The Birding Hour,

18:57.249 --> 18:59.683
and the guest tonight
is Dr. Richard Cooper,

18:59.752 --> 19:01.879
national expert on
the California Condor

19:01.954 --> 19:04.616
and author of
the bestselling book,
Keeper of the Souls.

19:05.324 --> 19:07.815
Please, Dr. Cooper,
this is fascinating.
Tell us some more.

19:07.893 --> 19:08.985
DR. COOPER:
They've been pulled back

19:09.061 --> 19:10.426
from the brink
of extinction a bit.

19:10.496 --> 19:11.758
They're hanging in there.

19:11.831 --> 19:14.994
The California Condor
has always captured
the imagination.

19:15.067 --> 19:17.467
A Native American
medicine man once said,

19:17.536 --> 19:20.164
''It's true that the
condor literally eats death.

19:20.239 --> 19:21.900
''But the great bird
is not sickened by this.

19:22.174 --> 19:23.436
''No, it has a secret.

19:23.509 --> 19:26.740
''It keeps the souls
of all the fallen creatures
it consumes.

19:26.812 --> 19:29.042
''And they are its treasure
and its protection.

19:29.114 --> 19:31.105
''And with each soul
it takes in and shelters

19:31.183 --> 19:32.775
it grows larger and wiser.

19:33.085 --> 19:36.486
''Too large and wise
to ever succumb
to death itself. ''

19:36.822 --> 19:37.982
RADIO HOST: Well,
we all know that

19:38.057 --> 19:39.524
the California Condor
was near extinction.

19:39.959 --> 19:42.291
It's so nice to hear
that they have
a fighting chance now.

19:42.561 --> 19:45.587
DR. COOPER: Oh,
they are surviving with the
help of some terrific people.

19:45.664 --> 19:49.293
And they have some
very interesting ways of
defending themselves, too.

19:49.368 --> 19:51.268
RADIO HOST: Really?
Could you share
some of those?

19:51.337 --> 19:52.326
DR. COOPER: Not on the radio.

19:54.874 --> 19:57.672
PENELOPE: And please
watch over the missionaries,
our soldiers in foreign lands,

19:57.743 --> 20:01.975
the President, Mom and Dad,
and especially the seven
of us, this day.

20:05.885 --> 20:08.410
ls this the year?
It feels like it.

20:11.490 --> 20:14.755
I know you can't tell me,
but please keep Bug safe.

20:16.195 --> 20:17.594
ln Jesus' name, amen.

20:21.967 --> 20:23.798
PENELOPE'S MOM:
Penelope! It's getting late.

20:23.869 --> 20:25.268
I'm coming!

20:27.139 --> 20:28.868
It's getting late.

20:32.011 --> 20:34.741
Thank you.
Message received.

20:38.417 --> 20:40.749
Crows, 10.
Snot-nosed kids, zip.

20:41.387 --> 20:42.718
Hey!

20:42.888 --> 20:44.116
Ass-wipe!

20:44.189 --> 20:47.352
Get your little butt to school
before I put my boot up it!

20:49.528 --> 20:51.860
Let's go! Now!

21:02.107 --> 21:04.200
Can you step back
a little bit, Quint?

21:04.276 --> 21:06.972
What's the matter?
Don't you trust me?

21:08.747 --> 21:10.078
Of course I trust you.

21:16.722 --> 21:19.816
Don't trust anyone,
you dumb shit.

21:19.892 --> 21:20.881
(LAUGHS)

21:22.161 --> 21:24.095
Thanks, Quint.
Felt good.

21:24.163 --> 21:25.221
Anytime!

21:30.402 --> 21:31.960
(PHONE RINGING)

21:35.007 --> 21:36.338
I know you want me,
Brittany.

21:37.943 --> 21:39.672
Speaking.
I've got today's
assignment, Brandon.

21:39.745 --> 21:40.734
Got paper and pen?

21:40.813 --> 21:42.508
Of course I do.

21:42.581 --> 21:44.014
Bug Hellerman, three.

21:44.083 --> 21:45.311
Bug?

21:45.484 --> 21:47.509
Alex Dunkelman, eight.
I need it done this morning.

21:47.586 --> 21:48.644
Alex gets an eight?

21:48.821 --> 21:50.618
You have a problem
with that?

21:50.689 --> 21:53.522
No, it's just that
it's pretty high on Fang's
punitive scale.

21:53.592 --> 21:56.652
Usually, giving an eight
to the son of a felon

21:57.463 --> 21:59.363
comes with a bonus, is all.

21:59.431 --> 22:00.955
Don't say something
stupid, Brandon.

22:01.033 --> 22:02.057
Nothing big.

22:02.835 --> 22:04.234
A blowjob would do.

22:04.770 --> 22:08.672
How about I have
my dog bite it off and
bury it in my backyard?

22:09.475 --> 22:11.500
How big is your backyard?

22:12.444 --> 22:13.934
WOMAN ON RADIO:
Good morning, Riverton.

22:14.013 --> 22:17.073
It's hour 7
of Ripper Day 16.

22:17.149 --> 22:18.912
And we're talking
with Betty O'Neil,

22:18.984 --> 22:22.044
mother of Riverton
star quarterback,
Brandon O'Neil

22:22.121 --> 22:25.488
and head of the group,
Citizens for a Saner Riverton.

22:25.858 --> 22:28.588
Mrs. O'Neil,
why ban Ripper Day?

22:28.661 --> 22:30.925
It's just kids
having fun, isn't it?

22:30.996 --> 22:32.759
BETTY: No, it's not
kids having fun.

22:32.831 --> 22:34.059
It's kids having nightmares,

22:34.133 --> 22:36.601
seeing the Ripper
everywhere. Kids...

22:36.669 --> 22:37.761
(SCREAMING)

22:37.836 --> 22:41.203
Jumpy this morning, aren't we?
Where is the sock puppet?

22:41.573 --> 22:42.665
Where did you come from?

22:42.741 --> 22:43.765
Your window, where else?

22:43.842 --> 22:45.639
WOMAN ON RADIO:
ls Brandon damaged,
do you think?

22:45.711 --> 22:47.406
BETTY:
Of course Brandon isn't...

22:47.479 --> 22:48.537
What the fuck is that?

22:48.614 --> 22:49.706
Sock puppet.

22:49.782 --> 22:51.443
On steroids?

22:51.517 --> 22:53.348
Kind of.
Kind of?

22:53.419 --> 22:55.148
Only you wear it this time.

22:55.220 --> 22:57.279
What? Excuse me?

22:57.356 --> 22:59.688
BUG: Like Jay said,
''Shock and awe.''

23:02.861 --> 23:05.159
Thought Edgar
was a home crow.

23:05.364 --> 23:06.456
Raven.

23:06.532 --> 23:08.727
He's a guard.
He watches over you,
you know?

23:08.801 --> 23:11.167
You're still spooked
by last night, right?

23:11.236 --> 23:12.965
We were all watching
the river and he came
from the woods.

23:13.038 --> 23:14.096
That's scary.

23:14.173 --> 23:17.370
Now, that's Jay's whole thing.
Never do what they expect.

23:18.343 --> 23:21.210
And now we got Edgar up there
to keep him away. So...

23:21.280 --> 23:24.215
You can have him
if you want, after tonight.

23:24.717 --> 23:26.378
Edgar.
Seriously?

23:26.452 --> 23:28.317
Yeah. It's your birthday.

23:28.387 --> 23:30.446
Well, thanks.

23:30.522 --> 23:31.955
I should get
you a present.

23:32.024 --> 23:35.653
How about a weekend
in Las Vegas with
Brittany Cunningham?

23:36.228 --> 23:37.388
Brittany doesn't
know I'm alive.

23:37.463 --> 23:39.055
She's gonna,
after two days
and two nights

23:39.131 --> 23:41.691
of star-studded shows
and high-stakes gambling.

23:41.767 --> 23:43.166
Oh, yeah.

23:43.235 --> 23:45.760
Or I could just
help you with that.

23:46.171 --> 23:48.401
Yeah, that's just as good.

23:48.474 --> 23:49.532
It's heavy.

23:49.608 --> 23:51.041
It's all the fluids.

23:51.110 --> 23:52.304
Fluids?

23:52.377 --> 23:54.811
PENELOPE:
The Lord is my shepherd.
I shall not want.

23:54.880 --> 23:56.939
He leadeth me
beside the still waters.

23:57.015 --> 23:59.040
He restoreth my soul.

23:59.118 --> 24:02.246
Yea, though I walk
through the valley
of the shadow of death,

24:02.321 --> 24:04.846
I will fear no evil,
for thou art with me.

24:05.057 --> 24:08.424
Thou anointest
my head with oil.
My cup runneth over.

24:09.728 --> 24:12.128
Surely goodness and
mercy will follow me

24:12.197 --> 24:14.324
through all the
days of my life,

24:14.399 --> 24:18.392
and I will dwell
in the house of
the Lord forever.

24:18.470 --> 24:19.630
Amen.

24:25.778 --> 24:27.871
I know you're there, Lord.

24:28.113 --> 24:29.944
(CAWING)

24:31.984 --> 24:33.952
And I know you're here.

24:42.594 --> 24:44.118
(PHONE RINGING)

24:44.196 --> 24:46.061
BUG: Hello?
MAY: You like it?

24:46.131 --> 24:48.122
Yeah, it's great.
Thanks, Mom.

24:48.433 --> 24:49.991
I scotch-taped
your number to it.

24:50.269 --> 24:53.898
And mine, and 9-1-1.
Happy birthday, Bug.
I love you.

24:54.006 --> 24:55.530
Love you, too.

24:56.642 --> 24:58.701
How do...
Do I close it?

24:58.777 --> 25:01.644
Hit the red button.
Boom, done.

25:03.048 --> 25:04.140
Small!

25:04.216 --> 25:05.342
That bad?

25:05.417 --> 25:06.748
No, that's good.

25:06.819 --> 25:08.047
CHANDELLE: Jerome.

25:08.153 --> 25:09.245
Uh-oh.

25:09.321 --> 25:10.481
Get, Dunkelman.

25:10.556 --> 25:11.614
ALEX: Catch you
later, Jerome.

25:11.690 --> 25:13.180
What did I do now?
See you, Jerome.

25:13.258 --> 25:14.486
It's what you're
not going to do,

25:14.760 --> 25:16.387
which is hang
out with them.

25:16.461 --> 25:17.553
Why not?

25:18.230 --> 25:20.164
It's bad luck,
is ''why not.''

25:20.332 --> 25:21.492
Especially
on Ripper Day.

25:21.567 --> 25:24.593
You should totally
come some year, Fang.
It was wild!

25:24.670 --> 25:26.604
Like, Brandon set Bug up
to fight the monster,

25:26.672 --> 25:28.731
which was huge, by the way.

25:28.807 --> 25:31.298
And Bug,
he was so scared.

25:31.376 --> 25:34.470
Brandon didn't set
Bug up. I did.

25:35.480 --> 25:36.777
Do you know how to
steam open an envelope

25:36.849 --> 25:38.077
so it doesn't show?

25:38.150 --> 25:39.378
Put it in the freezer
for an hour.

25:39.451 --> 25:41.476
It opens itself and
reseals perfectly.

25:44.289 --> 25:45.278
This is to Bug.

25:46.491 --> 25:47.719
Oh, really?

25:48.827 --> 25:50.419
Here they come.

25:52.097 --> 25:53.621
Hold up, boys.
What do you got there?

25:53.899 --> 25:55.628
Happy birthday, insect.

25:55.701 --> 25:56.929
(DIALING)

25:57.002 --> 25:58.299
Clueless as usual.

25:58.837 --> 25:59.861
Go.

26:00.038 --> 26:02.802
Mr. Kaiser,
sixth period biology.

26:03.208 --> 26:04.937
It'll be there.

26:05.010 --> 26:06.272
Thanks, Jose.

26:06.345 --> 26:07.903
So, you want to
come over tonight?

26:07.980 --> 26:10.847
We could burn the house down
with my stepfather in it.

26:10.916 --> 26:13.180
(SARCASTlCALLY)
Ha, ha, ha!

26:13.252 --> 26:14.241
He give you anything
for your birthday?

26:14.319 --> 26:15.377
Yeah, a hematoma.

26:16.521 --> 26:18.386
Made it himself, too.

26:19.124 --> 26:20.148
Oh!

26:20.225 --> 26:24.389
Behold, Bug,
what light in yonder
window breaks.

26:26.064 --> 26:28.532
She is so beautiful.

26:28.600 --> 26:30.568
She's hot
for you, too.

26:31.436 --> 26:33.233
You should go over
there and talk to her.

26:33.305 --> 26:34.897
Excuse me,
Officer Ramirez.

26:34.973 --> 26:36.531
Maria told me you know
all about baseball.

26:36.608 --> 26:37.666
Mmm-hmm.
Uh-oh.

26:37.743 --> 26:38.869
RAMlREZ: What do
you want to know?

26:38.944 --> 26:40.104
Distraction maneuver.
Run!

26:42.347 --> 26:44.679
Bug. This is a three.

26:45.417 --> 26:47.612
Dunkelman,
this is an eight.

26:47.686 --> 26:49.051
(GRUNTS)

26:49.721 --> 26:52.121
That's the way
the cookie crumbles.

26:52.190 --> 26:53.521
Dunkelman,

26:53.625 --> 26:56.150
stay away from
the Fang Zone.

26:56.228 --> 26:58.628
And you,
you stay away from him.

27:00.966 --> 27:02.126
ALEX: Thanks, Brandon.

27:02.301 --> 27:03.427
Felt good.

27:03.735 --> 27:05.134
BRANDON: Ass-wipe.

27:05.203 --> 27:08.468
Not as good as your mother
felt last night, though.

27:10.142 --> 27:12.076
Just bought yourself a 20.

27:12.144 --> 27:13.202
Brandon O'Neil.

27:15.080 --> 27:17.674
Do not bring the wrath
of Jehovah down upon you.

27:17.950 --> 27:21.215
Your sins are already
a stench in the nostrils
of an angry God.

27:21.286 --> 27:23.516
Like knocking up
Melanie Pratt,
who's only 15

27:23.588 --> 27:25.522
and the principal's daughter.

27:25.590 --> 27:27.182
What? Melanie's pregnant?

27:27.259 --> 27:29.159
She's in my
prayer group. Duh!

27:29.227 --> 27:30.489
What men will do
to you in prison

27:30.562 --> 27:33.292
is nothing compared
to what demons will
do to you in Hell.

27:33.498 --> 27:35.728
On beds of fire.
Through all eternity.

27:36.335 --> 27:38.200
I'm going to get you
for this, Penelope.

27:38.470 --> 27:41.234
If you do, God will
get you, Brandon,
and it won't be pretty.

